# ZenStudy — Environment Variables Template
#
# Copy this file to .env.local and fill in your credentials.
# .env.local is git-ignored and must never be committed.
#
# MOCK MODE: Leaving all VITE_FIREBASE_* variables empty (or not creating
# .env.local at all) runs the app in MOCK MODE — auth and data fall back to
# localStorage so the app is fully navigable with zero backend setup.
# This satisfies AUTH-06 / SET-02 for examiner demos.
#
# LIVE MODE: Populate all VITE_FIREBASE_* variables from your Firebase
# project console (Project Settings > General > Your apps > SDK setup).
# NOTE: The VITE_GEMINI_API_KEY is intentionally not a VITE_ bundled var
# to avoid leaking it into the client bundle. Wire it via the in-app
# Settings panel (Phase 4) instead of here.

# Firebase — Web App Config
VITE_FIREBASE_API_KEY=
VITE_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=
VITE_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=
VITE_FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET=
VITE_FIREBASE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID=
VITE_FIREBASE_APP_ID=

# Gemini — API Key (Phase 4 Settings panel; not bundled into client JS)
VITE_GEMINI_API_KEY=
